 of the workforce, the information highway, work and the environment, and the possibilities of shorter work hours. Despite the cancellation of government funding for further research, Re Shaping Work 2 sheds new light on crucial issues of the changing nature of work and technology. Re Shaping Work 2 is a book of great interest to students of workplace change, labour studies, and industrial relations, as well as trade unionists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aCoursebook. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, John , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAnderson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEaton, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHadley, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewchuk, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobertson, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchenk, Chris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchenk, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSobel, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144260292240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442602922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442602922.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ES